# 🔍 File Identifier

A fast CLI tool to detect file types using **magic numbers** — not extensions.

> Useful for identifying real file formats, even when extensions are missing or misleading (e.g., `.pdf.exe`).

---

## 🚀 Install

```bash
pip install file-identifier
```

---

## ⚡ Usage

```bash
file-identifier <file_path>
```

Example:

```bash
file-identifier "C:\Users\YourName\Downloads\file.zip"
```

---

## 📦 Features

* Detects real file type from binary signatures
* Works without relying on extensions
* Supports images, documents, archives, media & executables
* Fast and lightweight

